    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Cornelis De Schrijver to Miklós Oláh (Antwerp, 18 October
                    1536)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He has read Oláh’s poem three or four times, but he has not found
                            anything wrong with it. He is responding to his poem with a poem; he
                            cannot write anything more serious now due to his hardships and worries.
                        </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Multo clarissimo domino Nicolao Olao Pannonio Transilvano theasaurario
                    Albensi Cornelius Scribonius Grapheus. </p>
                <p>Lepidissima tua legi carmina,<note type="critic">See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 589.</note> Humanissime Olae, atque
                    iterum terque quaterque relegi, neque quidquam (tenui quidem meo isto iudicio)
                    in eisdem deprehendi, quod nostra, quam a me exigis, censura egeat. Ad ea tua
                    lepidissima, quali quali <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">meo</add> carmine
                        respondeo;<note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap">Ipolyi</hi> 1875,
                        590–592.</note> graviora aliquando scribere non deest animus et quidem
                    ardentissimus, sed egestas et curae, egestatis filiae, id non sinunt.
                    Quandoquidem est mihi munus quoddam publicum, quod vix mihi sufficit quotannis
                    sexaginta Florenorum Carolinorum et id quidem permolestum. Qui igitur
                    gravioribus Musis incumbere possem non video, nisi alicunde felicior mihi
                    aspiret Favonius. Vale, Clarissime Olae. </p>
                <p>Datae <placeName>Antverpiae</placeName> XVIII. Octobris anno a Christo
                    nato 1536. </p>
                <p
                    ><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>[Accipio
                    usque libens…]<?oxy_custom_end?><note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 590–592. In Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Albu–Capoianu</hi> 1974, 161–163.</note></p>
            </div>
        </body>
